      "Another case of this, from [our chat](https://surge.sh/help/chat)\n\n> node version: v0.12.7\n> npm version: 2.11.3\n> \n> Both windows 7 and windows 10 machines are pretty fresh installs, installed from MSDN bootable ISO\n> \n> mynameiswarren [3:42 PM]\n> Then installed NodeJS x64\n> \n> Yes, that's what I was initially trying... on Windows 10 I'm seeing a \"Node.js command prompt\" under apps, both that and the default have the same issue though\n> \n> mynameiswarren [3:47 PM]\n> I have actually just got it to work... but only under my home directory, i.e. c:\\Users\\warren\\surge_test\n> \n> mynameiswarren [3:47 PM]\n> where as p:\\projects\\surge_test doesn't work\n> \n> mynameiswarren [3:47 PM]\n> even though I have full permissions\n> \n> when running \"surge\" under my user location, it appears to auto-flll the email and token, but on \"p\" email is initially blank\n> \n> kenneth [3:47 PM] \n> Oh interesting. `P:\\` is another drive you are on?\n> \n> mynameiswarren [3:48 PM]\n> yes, \"p\" is a local drive partition\n\nThis lines up with another instance of this where:\n- It wasn’t working while not on `C:\\`, also with full permissions.\n- It works with Git Bash but not the Node.js or Windows Command Prompt\n",
